<subSubSection id="77EC7DFD06899BFE24EA3C7493B4CCA3" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" type="description">
<paragraph id="3A75E83EED9BF61E2F12D66223F94ADD" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">
Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="B1023635712EC8C279C3191C3C1899EC" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Scleropoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E819148F9095C32167AAB95D1D4A7501" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">Scleropoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
steht den Gattungen 
<taxonomicName id="72217FF3CCA9D97C9911547F10B82E1D" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="05F398BD0203894624849AA7238BF551" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="600829616CCC0477939F02A5B15693DE" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D52655147810D77DD785F549448AB3C3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">Festuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sehr nahe und wird oft mit der einen oder andern Gattung vereinigt. 
<emphasis id="38B236B17FE0D97E8FCA9433EDBF8C91" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">
Von der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="141E91DC9AB4BADBCDEAFE50B3F85688" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Festuca</taxonomicName>
unterscheidet sich 
<taxonomicName id="B00D1AE7D3C25225F67C3A9D29353565" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Scleropoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Scleropoa</taxonomicName>
durch den runden Nabelfleck, von der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="1B2343FAFD4ADBFF80C4BFE37FE6645D" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Poa</taxonomicName>
durch habituelle Merkmale.
</emphasis>
Wir belassen unsere einzige Art, 
<taxonomicName id="2DA7F0806718BE8F1C61E66EB7344D26" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Dryopteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigida">
<emphasis id="845FE9E452A60580341F6F08950FDC1D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">S. rigida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in dieser Gattung und lassen die Frage 
<normalizedToken id="90527305F3A2B7BEDC49B0B72E89D3D4" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">ueber</normalizedToken>
die 
<normalizedToken id="245CE20B28D15C5CF9E5ECFEAFF81AA0" originalValue="Zugehörigkeit" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">Zugehoerigkeit</normalizedToken>
mediterraner, kaukasischer und zentralasiatischer Arten zur Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="5CB8BA7ADE8E8062D7C8C0A6EFBEFCFE" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Scleropoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="318" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57F25B9C394CD3686D70A54A17E827D1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="318">Scleropoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
offen.
</paragraph>
